-- Spain Cuts Target for Renewable Energy Production by 7%, Expansion Reports
-- Ben Sills
-- 2010-06-15T05:39:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-15/spain-cuts-target-for-renewable-energy-production-by-7-expansion-reports.html

          
          
             The Spanish government will reduce 
its target for renewable energy production by about 7 percent 
when it presents its power generation strategy to the European 
Commission this month, Expansion reported.   
 Spain will aim to increase clean power capacity to 70 
gigawatts by 2020 from 40 GW at the end of 2009, compared with 
a previous goal of 75 GW, the newspaper said.   
 The objective for solar energy will be cut to 13.4 GW from 
15.7 GW while the target for offshore wind power will be cut to
3 GW from 5 GW, the newspaper said citing a draft of the plan.   
